title: Sidewall, 1875–85
creditline: Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt
description: Horizontal rectangle giving a complete width. Design of Chinese inspiration, with plants springing from vases and forming foliate arabesques set with scrolled ribbons and flowers, printed on black ground.
